                                                     Bengal start favourites
            A STAFF REPORTER            Shukla                           
	Calcutta: Yet to overcome the shock of all-rounder Avik Chowdhurys accident, Bengal will be hoping to begin their campaign in the Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy on a positive note when they take on Assam in Dhanbad on Wednesday.         
	Bengals performances this season so far has been anything but satisfactory being eliminated from the group stages of the two tournaments  Moin-ud Dowlah Gold Cup and the JP Atray Memorial Trophy  they have played so far.         
	The squad reached Dhanbad Tuesday afternoon and had a brief practice session. Their departure, scheduled for Monday, got delayed by a day because of Chowdhurys accident.         
	The Laxmi Ratan Shukla-led side is well balanced and with the likes of Deep Dasgupta and Abhishek Jhunjhunwala coming into the team, they are among the favourites of the East Zone Twenty20 meet. Bengal had played two practice matches, with former India captain Sourav Ganguly playing in the last one.         
	The experience will help the youngsters learn That is the idea of having such practice matches, coach Roger Binny said before leaving for Dhanbad.         
	Speaking about the match, Shukla said: We hope to do well tomorrow (Wednesday) But in T20 what matters is how you perform on the day. Assam are a good side but we are confident.         
	We havent decided on the team combination Once we have a look at the pitch, we will decide whether to go in with two spinners or three pacers, he added.         
	Wriddhiman Saha will don the wicketkeepers role while Deep and the young Sreevats Goswami are set to be included as batsmen.         
	Though Shukla said that the team was satisfied with the ground, team manager Robert Rozario informed that the outfield was a bit uneven.         
	Assam boast of the experience of Amol Mazumdar and Sairaj Bahutule. They will also bank on the talented all-rounder Dhiraj Goswami.                                                                                                                       
